og sculpture, and the architectural experiments of Tange Lab and the Metabolists, who sought to design climate-controlled capsule housing and domed cities. Furuhata’s transpacific analysis offers a novel take on the elemental conditions of media and climate change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszJapan. 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszUnited States. 0aDigital mediaxEnvironmental aspectszJapan. 0aDigital mediaxEnvironmental aspectszUnited States. 0aWeather controlxSocial aspectszJapan. 0aWeather controlxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aWeather controlxTechnological innovationsxEnvironmental aspectszJapan. 0aWeather controlxTechnological innovationsxEnvironmental aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022435zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022435423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022435/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles